#. Tag: title
#: smt_overview.xml:9
#, no-c-format
msgid "About This Guide"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_overview.xml:11
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&smtool; (&smt;) for &sle;&nbsp;12 SP2 allows enterprise customers to "
"optimize the management of &sle; software updates and subscription "
"entitlements. It establishes a proxy system for &sccreg; with repository "
"(formerly known as 'catalog') and registration targets. This helps you "
"centrally manage software updates within the firewall on a per-system basis, "
"while maintaining your corporate security policies and regulatory compliance."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_overview.xml:19
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&smt; allows you to provision updates for all of your devices running a "
"product based on &sle;. By downloading these updates only once and "
"distributing them throughout the enterprise, you can set more restrictive "
"firewall policies and, where applicable, avoid significant network usage "
"stemming from repeated downloads of the same updates by each device. The "
"tool is fully supported and available as a download to customers with an "
"active &sle; product subscription."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_overview.xml:28
#, no-c-format
msgid "&smtool; is a good choice for you if you:"
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_overview.xml:33
#, no-c-format
msgid "need one tool that updates both &sle; and &rhel; servers."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_overview.xml:38
#, no-c-format
msgid "want to have a good overview of your company's license compliance."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_overview.xml:43
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"do not want to connect all your machines to &scc; to register and retrieve "
"updates, for bandwidth or security reasons."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_overview.xml:49
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"have &sle; hosts that are restricted and difficult to update without having "
"to invent your own update management solutions."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_overview.xml:55
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"need to integrate additional software update repositories (either external "
"or internal) into your update solution."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_overview.xml:61
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"want an out-of-the box staging solution for testing updates before releasing "
"them to the clients."
msgstr ""

#. Tag: para
#: smt_overview.xml:67
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"want to have a quick overview of the patch status of your &sle; servers and "
"desktops."
msgstr ""

